InstanceOfMVELFilter
public class MVELFilter<T>
extends Filter<T>

A Filter that implements its accept(InstructionContext) method by running a user-supplied MVEL script against the InstructionContext's current Object.

Author:
Laird Nelson

Method Detail

accept

public boolean accept(InstructionContext<T> context)
Accepts or rejects the supplied InstructionContext during execution by making sure that it can be read from and that the accept(Object, Map) method also returns true.

Overrides:
accept in class Filter<T>
Parameters:
context - the InstructionContext in which this MVELFilter is running; must not be null
Returns:
true if and only if the supplied InstructionContext is not null, can be read from, and produces an Object that is not null; false in all other cases
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if context is null
CompileException - if the accept(Object, Map) method throws a CompileException
See Also:
accept(Object, Map)

accept

public boolean accept(T item,
                      Map<Object,Object> variables)
Returns true if the execution of the MVEL expression associated with this MVELFilter returned an Object equal to Boolean.TRUE when evaluated against the supplied item.

Parameters:
item - the Object that will serve as the context for the MVEL expression associated with this MVELFilter during its evaluation; may be null
variables - a Map of variables that may be affected by the MVEL expression associated with this MVELFilter; may be null in which case a new HashMap will be used instead
Returns:
true if the execution of the MVEL expression associated with this MVELFilter returned an Object equal to Boolean.TRUE when evaluated against the supplied item; false otherwise
Throws:
CompileException - if the mvelExpression field's value could be compiled, but referenced an object or a property that could not be resolved during execution; thrown by the MVEL.executeExpression(Object, Object, VariableResolverFactory) method
